Barring a last minute ditch,the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) is set to approach the Supreme Court to demand  a review of its judgements in the 2019 presidential election petition in which it declared President Muhammadu Buhari of the All Progressives Congress (APC) winner. The decision of the party’s National Working Committee was predicated on the resolve of the APC to seek review of the apex court verdict on Zamfara and Bayelsa states governorship election petitions. READ ALSO: Kebbi offers scholarship, healthcare to children of soldiers The PDP national publicity secretary, Kola Ologbondiyan at a press briefing Monday evening said the party is also seeking review of judgements in respect of Kano, Katsina, Kaduna and Osun states. Details later…